BEIJING, Dec. 17 (Xinhua) -- Writer Tie Ning was reelected Friday as chairperson of the China Federation of Literary and Art Circles (CFLAC) and the China Writers Association (CWA). The 11th National Congress of the CFLAC and the 10th National Congress of the CWA concluded on Friday. When delivering her closing remarks, Tie vowed to provide a better environment for the prosperity and development of literature and art and build better conditions for writers and artists to create their works. Born in 1957, Tie started publishing her writings in the 1970s, and many of her works revolved around the aspirations of ordinary people. Her novel "Ah, Xiangxue," a short story and one of her most acclaimed works, centered on a country girl's yearning for the outside world and modern civilization. Tie was first elected chairperson of the CWA in 2006. Enditem